WEBVTT

00:01:29.460 --> 00:01:34.890
[Our Dazzling Days]

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:37.690
[Episode 30]

00:01:39.590 --> 00:01:41.200
No, where are you taking me?

00:01:41.430 --> 00:01:42.710
You'll see.

00:01:42.710 --> 00:01:43.590
See what?

00:01:43.830 --> 00:01:44.960
What is there to see?

00:01:54.229 --> 00:01:55.430
What's going on here?

00:02:02.840 --> 00:02:04.310
What does this mean?

00:02:04.560 --> 00:02:05.120
Look.

00:02:05.240 --> 00:02:06.960
[Retirement Ceremony of Comrade Yan Wenyuan
at East Integrated Chemical Plant]

00:02:06.960 --> 00:02:08.789
Congratulations on your retirement.

00:02:08.789 --> 00:02:10.050
Why didn't you tell me?

00:02:10.240 --> 00:02:12.030
Alright, comrades.

00:02:12.870 --> 00:02:15.000
Today is the day Comrade Yan Wenyuan,

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:16.590
Chief Technical Engineer
of our East Chemical Plant,

00:02:16.590 --> 00:02:19.680
is honorably retiring.

00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:22.200
Bravo!

00:02:23.930 --> 00:02:25.120
From a technician to chief engineer,

00:02:25.120 --> 00:02:27.680
over the past 40 years,

00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:28.590
Comrade Yan

00:02:29.120 --> 00:02:31.280
has been a guiding light for everyone

00:02:31.280 --> 00:02:32.750
at East Chemical Plant!

00:02:32.750 --> 00:02:35.280
Bravo!

00:02:36.430 --> 00:02:37.030
Now,

00:02:37.030 --> 00:02:38.890
let's invite the star of the show,

00:02:39.030 --> 00:02:40.590
Comrade Yan Wenyuan,
to come up and say a few words.

00:02:40.590 --> 00:02:41.920
Bravo! Speech!

00:02:41.940 --> 00:02:43.500
Bravo! Bravo!

00:02:47.910 --> 00:02:50.280
You really sprang a surprise on me.

00:02:50.630 --> 00:02:52.190
This rascal didn't tell me.

00:02:53.500 --> 00:02:54.530
What should I say?

00:02:55.150 --> 00:02:56.360
I haven't prepared anything.

00:02:56.360 --> 00:02:58.150
Just speak off the cuff!

00:02:58.150 --> 00:03:00.280
I'm now really confused.

00:03:00.670 --> 00:03:02.800
Her mother already says I'm confused.

00:03:04.400 --> 00:03:06.870
These days, when I come to the plant,

00:03:07.240 --> 00:03:08.680
I see people

00:03:10.060 --> 00:03:12.520
I recognize
but can't remember their names.

00:03:13.350 --> 00:03:15.210
The ones whose names I do remember

00:03:16.290 --> 00:03:17.420
I can't see anymore.

00:03:18.079 --> 00:03:19.079
I now think of

00:03:20.360 --> 00:03:21.150
the old days

00:03:22.280 --> 00:03:24.740
when we were rushing to repair
that reactor.

00:03:25.710 --> 00:03:27.970
The temperature inside was way too high,

00:03:28.060 --> 00:03:29.560
and someone had to step forward.

00:03:29.560 --> 00:03:31.620
The first one who stepped forward...

00:03:33.590 --> 00:03:34.520
was Zhao Zhiwei.

00:03:38.610 --> 00:03:39.610
He didn't make it.

00:03:41.710 --> 00:03:45.000
And the year
we were hoisting this reaction tower.

00:03:47.450 --> 00:03:50.490
Our equipment back then

00:03:50.710 --> 00:03:51.630
wasn't good enough.

00:03:51.630 --> 00:03:53.310
People had to go up.

00:03:53.560 --> 00:03:55.150
Everyone did.

00:03:55.670 --> 00:03:57.870
But unexpectedly, a slip-up happened,

00:03:58.079 --> 00:03:59.540
and an accident occurred.

00:04:01.030 --> 00:04:01.960
Jia Yulan,

00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:05.770
a technician who had just arrived—

00:04:06.870 --> 00:04:08.190
she was a woman,

00:04:09.800 --> 00:04:10.960
32 years old.

00:04:14.240 --> 00:04:14.840
Oh, right.

00:04:17.010 --> 00:04:18.720
There's a date I'll never forget:

00:04:18.720 --> 00:04:21.680
September 17, 1980.

00:04:22.120 --> 00:04:23.800
It was a Wednesday,

00:04:24.800 --> 00:04:26.600
again repairing the reactor.

00:04:27.190 --> 00:04:29.000
The hospital called me,

00:04:29.190 --> 00:04:31.520
saying her mother was about to give birth.

00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:33.190
On one hand, my baby was on the way;

00:04:33.190 --> 00:04:34.390
on the other hand,
there was a repair job to do.

00:04:34.390 --> 00:04:35.800
Both were equally important.

00:04:35.800 --> 00:04:36.659
What could I do?

00:04:37.820 --> 00:04:39.630
It was Ding.

00:04:39.730 --> 00:04:41.600
Back then, he was still a young man.

00:04:41.600 --> 00:04:42.510
He came up with an idea.

00:04:42.510 --> 00:04:44.750
He tied a red ribbon to the machine,

00:04:44.750 --> 00:04:46.280
saying it would bring luck.

00:04:47.390 --> 00:04:48.870
And it actually worked.

00:04:49.390 --> 00:04:51.000
After the repairs,

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:52.310
I still made it to the hospital.

00:04:52.310 --> 00:04:54.800
I didn't miss the first cry
of my daughter.

00:04:55.800 --> 00:04:58.630
Later, I even kept
that ribbon as a keepsake.

00:04:59.950 --> 00:05:03.750
I added the character "Dan", which means red,
to my daughter's name.

00:05:04.750 --> 00:05:05.810
And just like that,

00:05:07.680 --> 00:05:10.680
we old pals went through life together.

00:05:13.420 --> 00:05:14.220
But I never...

00:05:15.560 --> 00:05:17.360
I never expected that in the end,

00:05:20.060 --> 00:05:22.740
the plant would shut down.

00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:27.230
Sometimes, when I'm alone,

00:05:29.160 --> 00:05:30.490
I like sitting up there.

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:33.720
At night,

00:05:34.230 --> 00:05:35.840
I looked at our plant.

00:05:36.550 --> 00:05:39.870
It looked like the plant was asleep.

00:05:40.700 --> 00:05:41.560
I just wondered

00:05:42.800 --> 00:05:43.830
when

00:05:45.430 --> 00:05:48.270
our plant would wake up.

00:05:49.600 --> 00:05:50.390
One year.

00:05:51.720 --> 00:05:52.800
Two years.

00:05:57.000 --> 00:05:58.120
Five years.

00:06:00.870 --> 00:06:02.270
We have to thank this kid.

00:06:04.480 --> 00:06:05.950
He made this plant

00:06:06.900 --> 00:06:08.190
wake up.

00:06:09.520 --> 00:06:11.030
It woke up!

00:06:19.630 --> 00:06:22.160
This pen has been with me all my life.

00:06:24.720 --> 00:06:26.240
I used this very pen

00:06:26.240 --> 00:06:27.640
to sign every blueprint.

00:06:27.920 --> 00:06:28.720
I guarantee,

00:06:28.920 --> 00:06:30.240
that for every blueprint,

00:06:30.240 --> 00:06:32.560
I signed with full responsibility.

00:06:35.630 --> 00:06:39.040
Today, I'm giving this pen to you.

00:06:49.159 --> 00:06:49.830
Son.

00:06:56.430 --> 00:06:57.890
I'm entrusting this plant

00:07:01.680 --> 00:07:04.360
and all the workers

00:07:09.870 --> 00:07:11.680
to you.

00:07:16.990 --> 00:07:18.550
Thank you.

00:07:29.960 --> 00:07:31.820
Don't worry, Chief Engineer Yan.

00:07:32.360 --> 00:07:34.490
I won't let everyone in the plant down.

00:07:35.680 --> 00:07:36.510
Bravo!

00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:39.270
Bravo! Bravo!

00:07:43.310 --> 00:07:44.120
Xia Lei,

00:07:45.390 --> 00:07:47.520
I haven't reached retirement age yet.

00:07:48.159 --> 00:07:49.560
I haven't forgotten

00:07:49.950 --> 00:07:51.000
any of my skills.

00:07:52.100 --> 00:07:53.300
If you need anything,

00:07:54.670 --> 00:07:55.630
just tell me.

00:08:05.070 --> 00:08:06.560
Comrade Ding Guoqiang.

00:08:09.710 --> 00:08:11.560
The plant officially orders you

00:08:12.680 --> 00:08:13.890
to return to your post immediately.

00:08:13.890 --> 00:08:16.170
Bravo! Bravo!

00:08:16.200 --> 00:08:16.800
Bravo!

00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:18.630
Bravo! Bravo!

00:08:22.750 --> 00:08:23.560
In the end,

00:08:24.270 --> 00:08:26.270
I'd like to quote Pavel Korchagin

00:08:26.270 --> 00:08:27.930
to conclude today's meeting.

00:08:28.680 --> 00:08:31.270
All my life and all my strength

00:08:31.560 --> 00:08:32.669
have been devoted to

00:08:32.669 --> 00:08:33.669
[East Integrated Chemical Plant,
Factory No. 3]

00:08:33.669 --> 00:08:35.929
the most magnificent cause in the world.

00:08:36.240 --> 00:08:37.120
For 40 years,

00:08:38.110 --> 00:08:40.169
all employees of East Chemical Plant

00:08:40.510 --> 00:08:42.240
have done right by our country,

00:08:42.270 --> 00:08:43.270
by ourselves,

00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:46.140
and by everyone at East Chemical Plant!

00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:47.960
Xia Lei.

00:08:48.510 --> 00:08:50.110
We haven't changed our sign.

00:08:50.510 --> 00:08:51.480
No, we haven't.

00:08:52.080 --> 00:08:53.280
And I can't change it.

00:08:53.320 --> 00:08:55.790
I just hope that from now on,

00:08:56.270 --> 00:08:58.480
we can continue to use this name

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:01.600
and also the spirit
of our East Chemical Plant.

00:09:01.600 --> 00:09:04.240
Bravo!

00:09:05.480 --> 00:09:06.750
Here today,

00:09:07.270 --> 00:09:09.030
we have veterans
of the East Chemical Plant

00:09:09.030 --> 00:09:11.150
as well as new recruits.

00:09:11.560 --> 00:09:12.780
Now that we are together,

00:09:12.780 --> 00:09:14.270
we must stand by each other,

00:09:14.270 --> 00:09:15.730
just like our fathers did.

00:09:16.120 --> 00:09:18.440
Upholding the spirit of Factory No. 3,

00:09:18.440 --> 00:09:20.670
we will surely achieve greatness again!

00:09:20.670 --> 00:09:22.320
Bravo!

00:09:22.600 --> 00:09:24.060
Achieve greatness again.

00:09:24.630 --> 00:09:26.060
Chief Engineer Yan, let's head in.

00:09:26.060 --> 00:09:27.560
Let's go. Let's go together.

00:09:27.560 --> 00:09:28.800
Okay. Let's go.

00:09:29.200 --> 00:09:29.750
Yan.

00:09:47.690 --> 00:09:48.620
You're cooking?

00:09:48.740 --> 00:09:49.470
You're back?

00:09:50.440 --> 00:09:51.500
I made steamed buns.

00:09:51.500 --> 00:09:52.300
Steamed buns?

00:09:52.570 --> 00:09:53.240
Let me see.

00:09:53.330 --> 00:09:55.190
Pickled cabbage filling. Don't!

00:09:56.200 --> 00:09:57.030
These buns are huge.

00:09:57.030 --> 00:09:59.080
Why lift the lid
while I'm steaming the buns?

00:09:59.080 --> 00:10:00.410
Why are you so annoying?

00:10:02.920 --> 00:10:04.460
The fire is good now. Stop fanning.

00:10:04.460 --> 00:10:05.960
I made so many buns today.

00:10:05.960 --> 00:10:07.810
I should have invited Mr. and Mrs. Ding

00:10:07.810 --> 00:10:08.930
over to eat with us.

00:10:09.680 --> 00:10:11.560
On my way back, I saw...

00:10:12.030 --> 00:10:12.960
Mr. Li.

00:10:14.360 --> 00:10:15.630
He was carrying a bag of dried tofu

00:10:15.630 --> 00:10:17.960
and heading home with some green onions.

00:10:17.960 --> 00:10:19.760
He's making do for dinner again.

00:10:20.470 --> 00:10:21.800
Once the buns are ready,

00:10:22.150 --> 00:10:23.610
I'll take some over to him.

00:10:23.750 --> 00:10:25.490
No problem. They're almost ready.

00:10:25.490 --> 00:10:27.450
Also, these past couple of days,

00:10:27.660 --> 00:10:28.720
I've been thinking

00:10:29.570 --> 00:10:32.830
that there are actually
a lot of old folks left at the plant.

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:35.550
These old folks...

00:10:35.550 --> 00:10:37.580
they all watched me grow up, right?

00:10:37.750 --> 00:10:40.010
They were all like uncles to me back then.

00:10:41.790 --> 00:10:44.190
When I was young,
I ate so much of their food.

00:10:44.740 --> 00:10:46.790
Shouldn't I

00:10:47.270 --> 00:10:49.800
take the responsibility
to take care of them?

00:10:49.870 --> 00:10:50.270
Right?

00:10:50.450 --> 00:10:51.100
Yes.

00:10:51.130 --> 00:10:52.530
It's time to give back.

00:10:52.550 --> 00:10:53.030
Right.

00:10:53.060 --> 00:10:54.050
I can't do anything big,

00:10:54.050 --> 00:10:56.310
but we should help with the small things.

00:10:56.640 --> 00:10:58.910
So I'm thinking
that in the future, when we cook,

00:10:58.910 --> 00:11:00.960
we should make a bit extra every day.

00:11:01.200 --> 00:11:02.840
Our pot is big enough anyway, right?

00:11:02.840 --> 00:11:04.240
Once it's ready, I'll...

00:11:04.240 --> 00:11:06.040
deliver some to these old folks.

00:11:06.150 --> 00:11:07.750
The stuff they eat all day...

00:11:08.760 --> 00:11:09.740
is too plain.

00:11:10.030 --> 00:11:11.410
No problem. I support you.

00:11:11.410 --> 00:11:14.670
That kid who used to mooch meals back then
has all grown up now.

00:11:14.670 --> 00:11:15.690
And he can deliver food to others.

00:11:15.690 --> 00:11:16.360
Yeah.

00:12:04.720 --> 00:12:06.050
Come on, Yan.

00:12:06.080 --> 00:12:07.410
Time for your medicine.

00:12:08.230 --> 00:12:09.360
Take your medicine.

00:12:13.650 --> 00:12:15.550
Who are you?

00:12:15.680 --> 00:12:16.870
Who do you think I am?

00:12:17.690 --> 00:12:18.690
I don't know you.

00:12:20.270 --> 00:12:21.750
I'm Xiaodan's mom.

00:12:23.100 --> 00:12:24.430
I'm your wife.

00:12:24.680 --> 00:12:26.480
Hurry up and take your medicine.

00:12:26.800 --> 00:12:28.510
How did you get into our house?

00:12:29.910 --> 00:12:31.570
Even if the door was unlocked,

00:12:32.310 --> 00:12:34.240
you shouldn't have just walked in.

00:12:35.820 --> 00:12:36.950
It's my mom, Dad.

00:12:37.650 --> 00:12:39.050
You know who I am, right?

00:12:39.810 --> 00:12:41.730
That's... my mom.

00:12:41.790 --> 00:12:43.720
No, no, no.

00:12:44.080 --> 00:12:45.910
Your mom is younger than her.

00:12:46.660 --> 00:12:49.410
She's prettier.

00:12:49.670 --> 00:12:51.080
She... She isn't her.

00:12:51.360 --> 00:12:52.270
You don't even recognize me now.

00:12:52.270 --> 00:12:53.130
Don't touch me.

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:55.390
Okay, I won't touch you.

00:12:55.870 --> 00:12:57.790
Sweetie, tell him to take his medicine.

00:12:57.790 --> 00:12:58.390
Okay.

00:13:01.860 --> 00:13:03.660
He'll be fine in a couple of days.

00:13:03.660 --> 00:13:05.320
-Yes, he will.
-He'll be fine.

00:13:13.080 --> 00:13:14.610
I've never seen her before.

00:13:29.320 --> 00:13:30.910
The recitation...

00:13:32.110 --> 00:13:35.750
of "To the Oak" by Yan Xiaodan

00:13:37.150 --> 00:13:41.200
won first prize.

00:13:43.310 --> 00:13:44.150
My...

00:13:45.240 --> 00:13:46.150
Daughter.

00:13:47.120 --> 00:13:48.480
My daughter.

00:13:49.240 --> 00:13:49.910
Xiaodan.

00:13:51.670 --> 00:13:53.550
So... so wonderful.

00:13:54.790 --> 00:13:56.720
That's because I'm your daughter.

00:14:43.550 --> 00:14:44.120
Dad.

00:14:44.750 --> 00:14:45.440
Look.

00:14:46.150 --> 00:14:49.070
In the future, this area you see

00:14:50.390 --> 00:14:53.050
will be turned into
a culture and creative park.

00:14:53.920 --> 00:14:54.920
By then,

00:14:55.750 --> 00:14:57.670
the Mahavira Hall you designed

00:14:58.200 --> 00:15:01.810
will serve as a landmark
for the Third Front Plant

00:15:03.190 --> 00:15:04.620
and remain forever.

00:15:08.390 --> 00:15:09.720
It won't be demolished.

00:15:14.840 --> 00:15:15.630
The...

00:15:16.510 --> 00:15:17.200
The Ma...

00:15:19.440 --> 00:15:21.510
M-Mahavira Hall...

00:15:23.200 --> 00:15:24.400
won't be demolished?

00:15:24.440 --> 00:15:25.170
No, it won't.

00:15:26.630 --> 00:15:27.440
Good.

00:15:28.980 --> 00:15:29.950
In the future,

00:15:29.970 --> 00:15:31.600
people from outside

00:15:32.110 --> 00:15:34.030
will come here to visit.

00:15:34.270 --> 00:15:36.390
That way, more people

00:15:36.390 --> 00:15:39.850
will know your contribution
to the Third Front Construction.

00:15:45.070 --> 00:15:46.830
In my whole life...

00:15:49.870 --> 00:15:50.550
Two...

00:15:52.120 --> 00:15:54.030
two contributions.

00:15:58.870 --> 00:15:59.910
There...

00:16:01.870 --> 00:16:02.440
There...

00:16:04.440 --> 00:16:05.480
What else?

00:16:19.030 --> 00:16:19.840
Baby.

00:16:35.430 --> 00:16:40.580
♪ Outside the walls,
the west wind rises, smoke drifts ♪

00:16:40.770 --> 00:16:45.010
♪ Lanterns sway gently ♪

00:16:45.670 --> 00:16:46.150
Go to work...

00:16:46.150 --> 00:16:48.430
♪ Cicadas sing tirelessly in the dusk ♪

00:16:48.430 --> 00:16:50.950
Fra-France.

00:16:51.270 --> 00:16:52.510
♪ The young run swiftly, without rest ♪

00:16:52.510 --> 00:16:54.590
Don't worry about me.

00:16:56.360 --> 00:16:57.040
I'm doing fine.

00:16:57.040 --> 00:17:02.390
♪ Time stretches long,
people travel 1,000 miles ♪

00:17:02.410 --> 00:17:03.240
♪ Looking back, the mountains are gone ♪

00:17:03.240 --> 00:17:05.240
Dad... Dad... you...

00:17:05.329 --> 00:17:06.930
You remembered everything?

00:17:07.280 --> 00:17:09.349
♪ Parting now,
the road to the horizon stretches on ♪

00:17:09.349 --> 00:17:11.069
Not... confused.

00:17:11.950 --> 00:17:12.810
Not confused.

00:17:12.810 --> 00:17:16.920
♪ Plum blossoms bloom again,
another year passes ♪

00:17:20.109 --> 00:17:21.200
Don't cry.

00:17:21.270 --> 00:17:21.829
Don't cry.

00:17:21.829 --> 00:17:23.000
Don't cry.

00:17:23.000 --> 00:17:23.829
Don't cry.

00:17:24.240 --> 00:17:25.030
I won't cry.

00:17:25.030 --> 00:17:25.550
Don't cry.

00:17:25.550 --> 00:17:28.349
Hug...

00:17:28.550 --> 00:17:29.070
Hug...

00:17:29.070 --> 00:17:30.310
Don't cry.

00:17:31.880 --> 00:17:32.640
Don't cry.

00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:34.960
Dad, don't cry.

00:17:39.620 --> 00:17:45.020
♪ Time stretches long,
people travel 1,000 miles ♪

00:17:45.050 --> 00:17:48.810
♪ Looking back, the mountains are gone ♪

00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:55.190
♪ Parting now,
the road to the horizon stretches on ♪

00:17:55.410 --> 00:17:57.160
♪ Plum blossoms bloom again,
another year passes ♪

00:17:57.160 --> 00:17:58.510
You clap once,

00:17:59.160 --> 00:18:01.070
I clap once.

00:18:01.070 --> 00:18:01.750
♪ Voices echo from the past ♪

00:18:01.750 --> 00:18:06.120
One child flies a plane.

00:18:06.380 --> 00:18:06.960
♪ In the neighborhood,
whose playful child races under the sun? ♪

00:18:06.960 --> 00:18:08.680
You clap twice,

00:18:09.550 --> 00:18:11.110
I clap twice.

00:18:11.660 --> 00:18:11.920
♪ Whispering your name, can you hear it? ♪

00:18:11.920 --> 00:18:15.880
Two children play toss-the-handkerchief.

00:18:16.550 --> 00:18:17.070
You clap three times,

00:18:17.070 --> 00:18:18.830
♪ Evening song plays ♪

00:18:18.830 --> 00:18:20.350
I clap three times.

00:18:21.070 --> 00:18:22.140
Three children eat cookies.

00:18:22.140 --> 00:18:25.480
♪ People gone, leaving only a lone shadow
in the setting sun ♪

00:18:25.480 --> 00:18:27.030
You clap four times,

00:18:27.550 --> 00:18:27.790
♪ Sighing, where is home? ♪

00:18:27.790 --> 00:18:29.160
I clap four times.

00:18:29.890 --> 00:18:33.610
Four children practice calligraphy.

00:18:35.830 --> 00:18:37.440
Attention, fellow workers.

00:18:38.070 --> 00:18:40.240
The vehicles
for the first batch of relocated personnel

00:18:40.240 --> 00:18:42.880
have already arrived
outside the family quarters.

00:18:42.880 --> 00:18:44.030
People

00:18:44.610 --> 00:18:47.760
in Buildings 20 to 28,

00:18:48.280 --> 00:18:49.640
please take your luggage...

00:18:49.640 --> 00:18:50.690
Goodbye. Take care.

00:18:50.690 --> 00:18:52.750
And go to the designated location...

00:18:53.790 --> 00:18:55.400
Attention, fellow workers.

00:18:56.720 --> 00:18:57.920
You're walking fast now.

00:18:57.920 --> 00:18:59.200
Don't you trust my work?

00:18:59.200 --> 00:19:00.030
You have to take everything!

00:19:00.030 --> 00:19:00.920
Take it if it's still usable.

00:19:00.920 --> 00:19:02.240
Here. Do you need this board?

00:19:02.240 --> 00:19:03.510
-Yes.
-Okay.

00:19:03.960 --> 00:19:05.200
Take it if it's usable.

00:19:05.200 --> 00:19:06.160
Why waste money?

00:19:06.160 --> 00:19:07.590
The vehicle has enough room for it.

00:19:07.590 --> 00:19:08.720
Is that everything?

00:19:08.890 --> 00:19:10.590
That's it. We're leaving the rest.

00:19:10.590 --> 00:19:11.070
Okay.

00:19:11.070 --> 00:19:12.330
I'm taking these down.

00:19:18.670 --> 00:19:19.270
Bye.

00:19:19.270 --> 00:19:20.200
Okay.

00:19:22.710 --> 00:19:23.510
-Alright.
-Bye.

00:19:23.510 --> 00:19:24.160
Alright. Go now.

00:19:24.160 --> 00:19:24.920
Okay. Take care.

00:19:24.920 --> 00:19:25.830
How do you feel?

00:19:27.350 --> 00:19:28.500
Quite sad.

00:19:29.680 --> 00:19:30.830
And a bit regretful

00:19:31.530 --> 00:19:33.390
that I couldn't record everyone.

00:19:35.010 --> 00:19:36.460
No one will forget them.

00:19:37.060 --> 00:19:37.780
No one will.

00:19:37.800 --> 00:19:38.870
We're heading over now.

00:19:38.870 --> 00:19:39.670
Okay. Bye.

00:19:41.570 --> 00:19:43.000
Let me know if anything happens here.

00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:43.480
Okay.

00:19:43.560 --> 00:19:44.850
Okay. Mr. Ding.

00:19:45.610 --> 00:19:46.160
Take care.

00:19:46.160 --> 00:19:47.110
Ding.

00:19:48.750 --> 00:19:50.680
-Keep in touch.
-Okay.

00:19:54.570 --> 00:19:58.170
♪ The Five-star Red Flag
flies high in the wind ♪

00:19:58.190 --> 00:20:02.220
♪ Songs of victory are heard all around ♪

00:20:02.360 --> 00:20:06.620
♪ We sing for our beloved motherland ♪

00:20:06.710 --> 00:20:09.110
♪ Now embarking on a path
to prosperity and strength ♪

00:20:09.110 --> 00:20:10.240
Old buddies!

00:20:10.630 --> 00:20:11.270
♪ We sing for our beloved motherland ♪

00:20:11.270 --> 00:20:13.730
We came here
listening to this song back then

00:20:13.960 --> 00:20:15.000
and built the East Chemical Plant
from scratch!

00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:17.240
♪ Now embarking on a path
to prosperity and strength ♪

00:20:17.240 --> 00:20:19.300
Today, we're singing this song again

00:20:19.780 --> 00:20:20.030
♪ We've crossed the mountains
and the plains ♪

00:20:20.030 --> 00:20:23.070
to send you off
to the new plant and a new life!

00:20:23.900 --> 00:20:26.310
♪ We've forged through the surging
Yellow River and Yangtze ♪

00:20:26.310 --> 00:20:27.030
Here...

00:20:28.170 --> 00:20:31.400
♪ This vast and beautiful land ♪

00:20:31.400 --> 00:20:32.500
will always be our home!

00:20:32.500 --> 00:20:34.500
♪ Is our dear hometown ♪

00:20:34.580 --> 00:20:38.480
♪ Smoke from the chimney drifted
back in those days ♪

00:20:38.880 --> 00:20:42.730
♪ Distant friends waving their hands ♪

00:20:43.070 --> 00:20:46.960
♪ From some yard wall comes a whistle ♪

00:20:47.150 --> 00:20:51.240
♪ Blowing the years running along ♪

00:20:51.780 --> 00:20:54.910
♪ You're always on my mind ♪

00:20:54.910 --> 00:20:55.500
Go now!

00:20:55.940 --> 00:20:56.000
♪ How are you doing now? ♪

00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:57.000
Ding, take care!

00:20:57.000 --> 00:20:58.550
Ding, take care! Ding!

00:20:58.790 --> 00:21:00.110
-Goodbye, Mr. Ding.
-Wherever we are,

00:21:00.110 --> 00:21:00.180
we are all family
from the East Chemical Plant.

00:21:00.180 --> 00:21:01.350
♪ Would you know me when we meet again? ♪

00:21:01.350 --> 00:21:02.350
Keep in touch!

00:21:04.470 --> 00:21:08.580
♪ I grew tall through all the goodbyes ♪

00:21:10.650 --> 00:21:14.390
♪ The one who wept with longing ♪

00:21:14.560 --> 00:21:18.240
♪ Home is where your heart
stays attached ♪

00:21:18.870 --> 00:21:21.010
♪ Those cheeks flushed red in heavy snow ♪

00:21:21.010 --> 00:21:23.170
[East Integrated Chemical Plant]

00:21:23.170 --> 00:21:27.150
♪ The smoke that rose to welcome me home ♪

00:21:27.710 --> 00:21:31.660
♪ The one I saw just by turning around ♪

00:21:31.770 --> 00:21:35.310
♪ Home is where the door's left open
for me ♪

00:21:36.110 --> 00:21:40.400
♪ Trains keep rushing forward nonstop ♪

00:21:40.450 --> 00:21:40.970
♪ But I go against the signs to find her ♪

00:21:40.970 --> 00:21:42.700
Come on. Come up and have a look.

00:21:44.380 --> 00:21:46.040
Oh my gosh. Look at this place.

00:21:46.550 --> 00:21:47.680
It's such a mess.

00:21:47.680 --> 00:21:48.400
This smell.

00:21:51.270 --> 00:21:51.870
It smells.

00:21:53.110 --> 00:21:54.570
I used to wonder back then.

00:21:55.200 --> 00:21:57.400
With such small lockers,

00:21:57.400 --> 00:22:00.060
how did we stuff those big winter coats
in there?

00:22:00.830 --> 00:22:02.030
I was wondering, too.

00:22:02.240 --> 00:22:04.070
With so many people in our plant,

00:22:04.370 --> 00:22:06.450
how did this bathhouse fit everyone?

00:22:08.110 --> 00:22:09.750
When it was crowded,
it was like dumplings in a pot.

00:22:09.750 --> 00:22:10.960
We were packed like sardines.

00:22:10.960 --> 00:22:13.830
Yeah. Once you came in from outside,

00:22:14.200 --> 00:22:15.000
you felt

00:22:15.400 --> 00:22:17.590
warm all over, inside and out.

00:22:17.830 --> 00:22:20.640
When you were studying in Shanghai,

00:22:21.750 --> 00:22:24.080
dragged me here to soak
every time you got back.

00:22:24.080 --> 00:22:24.990
Every time it took us a whole afternoon.

00:22:24.990 --> 00:22:26.380
I didn't know what you wanted to do.

00:22:26.380 --> 00:22:27.780
Who else could I look for?

00:22:27.790 --> 00:22:30.110
After I transferred to the school
at this plant,

00:22:30.110 --> 00:22:32.710
you were the first person
to take a bath with me.

00:22:33.110 --> 00:22:33.910
Right.

00:22:35.140 --> 00:22:38.420
Since then,
your dad always took us to bathe.

00:22:40.270 --> 00:22:40.840
Yeah.

00:22:42.110 --> 00:22:43.310
Let's go look inside.

00:22:44.140 --> 00:22:44.730
Xiaoman.

00:22:45.240 --> 00:22:47.830
When did our bathhouse close down?

00:22:48.700 --> 00:22:49.310
I don't know.

00:22:49.310 --> 00:22:51.710
It had closed
before I came back from Japan.

00:22:52.240 --> 00:22:53.510
It must have been years.

00:22:53.510 --> 00:22:55.310
Look at all the dust on the floor.

00:22:57.450 --> 00:22:58.620
Gosh, I'm choking.

00:23:04.670 --> 00:23:05.550
Let me tell you.

00:23:06.240 --> 00:23:07.550
When I was in Japan,

00:23:07.830 --> 00:23:09.200
they also took baths.

00:23:09.200 --> 00:23:10.200
They also had big hot springs.

00:23:10.200 --> 00:23:11.810
But their pools
were much smaller than ours.

00:23:11.810 --> 00:23:13.810
They weren't even on the same scale.

00:23:13.960 --> 00:23:15.290
Home is always the best.

00:23:27.640 --> 00:23:28.640
Remember this?

00:23:28.640 --> 00:23:29.270
I do.

00:23:29.480 --> 00:23:31.200
You've never won at this.

00:23:31.510 --> 00:23:32.790
You're so childish.

00:23:33.240 --> 00:23:34.240
Let's give it a go.

00:23:34.740 --> 00:23:35.430
Come on.

00:23:40.730 --> 00:23:42.500
I should just kick you down.

00:23:52.070 --> 00:23:53.330
As the old saying goes,

00:23:53.870 --> 00:23:56.670
from death comes life and wealth,

00:23:57.550 --> 00:23:58.540
and a house full of children.

00:23:58.540 --> 00:24:00.790
[Late Yan Wenyuan]

00:24:00.790 --> 00:24:01.590
Yan,

00:24:01.990 --> 00:24:03.450
I've poured you some wine.

00:24:20.550 --> 00:24:21.160
Dad,

00:24:22.620 --> 00:24:24.150
everyone is here to see you.

00:24:40.400 --> 00:24:41.000
Here.

00:24:47.950 --> 00:24:48.740
Yan.

00:24:51.070 --> 00:24:52.870
The times produce their heroes.

00:24:55.270 --> 00:24:57.930
You made countless contributions
to the plant.

00:24:59.110 --> 00:25:00.910
Even when you were ill this time,

00:25:02.270 --> 00:25:04.530
you were still thinking about the plant.

00:25:07.960 --> 00:25:09.960
We all understand your dedication.

00:25:11.440 --> 00:25:12.240
Rest in peace.

00:25:14.880 --> 00:25:15.810
Rest in peace...

00:25:17.760 --> 00:25:18.620
my good leader.

00:25:58.070 --> 00:25:59.000
My condolences.

00:25:59.610 --> 00:26:00.410
Take a bow.

00:26:00.830 --> 00:26:01.510
Son.

00:26:02.230 --> 00:26:03.890
Let's go burn the paper money.

00:26:09.820 --> 00:26:10.690
Yan.

00:26:13.240 --> 00:26:15.070
I'll visit you often, Yan.

00:26:16.420 --> 00:26:17.260
Yan...

00:26:30.710 --> 00:26:32.780
Grandma, Grandpa, I'm here to see you.

00:26:32.780 --> 00:26:34.780
[Tomb of Father, Zhang Hansheng,
and Mother, He Yuexiang]

00:26:35.440 --> 00:26:37.350
Why do these leaves fall so fast?

00:26:38.920 --> 00:26:41.650
It's only been a few days,
and it's covered again.

00:26:42.920 --> 00:26:45.120
Here. Set up the offerings for Grandma.

00:26:47.030 --> 00:26:47.640
Grandma,

00:26:48.500 --> 00:26:49.730
this is Chunchun.

00:26:49.810 --> 00:26:51.750
You haven't seen her before, right?

00:26:51.750 --> 00:26:55.990
We started a moving company together.

00:26:57.070 --> 00:26:58.530
Everything is going well.

00:26:59.350 --> 00:27:01.590
Life is getting better and better.

00:27:02.470 --> 00:27:04.990
So I brought Chunchun to meet you today.

00:27:06.180 --> 00:27:06.820
Right?

00:27:10.270 --> 00:27:10.920
Grandma.

00:27:13.200 --> 00:27:15.210
Chief Engineer Yan has passed away too.

00:27:15.210 --> 00:27:16.610
He just moved here today.

00:27:19.880 --> 00:27:21.410
Mr. Ding is getting old too.

00:27:22.030 --> 00:27:22.880
But it's okay.

00:27:23.350 --> 00:27:24.350
We are still here.

00:27:25.440 --> 00:27:27.880
We'll definitely
make life better and better.

00:27:27.880 --> 00:27:29.740
I'm not going anywhere, Grandma.

00:27:30.140 --> 00:27:31.400
I'll stay here forever

00:27:32.440 --> 00:27:33.550
in our plant.

00:27:34.790 --> 00:27:37.720
No matter who comes back, I'll be here.

00:28:00.510 --> 00:28:02.110
Hello, Grandma and Grandpa.

00:28:02.340 --> 00:28:03.820
I am Ye Chunchun.

00:28:05.030 --> 00:28:08.270
Please entrust Xiaoman to me from now on.

00:28:08.460 --> 00:28:10.630
I promise I'll take good care of him.

00:28:11.330 --> 00:28:12.990
I'll definitely work with him

00:28:14.090 --> 00:28:15.760
to build a happy home.

00:28:17.400 --> 00:28:18.270
Don't worry.

00:28:24.230 --> 00:28:25.830
Why are you saying this here?

00:28:49.150 --> 00:28:50.610
How's Factory No. 3 doing?

00:28:51.790 --> 00:28:54.250
We've upgraded the products and equipment.

00:28:57.310 --> 00:29:02.160
We plan to start production
by the end of the year.

00:29:02.720 --> 00:29:03.750
That's great.

00:29:04.000 --> 00:29:05.160
Congratulations.

00:29:05.750 --> 00:29:07.200
You managed to keep

00:29:07.680 --> 00:29:09.440
the plant's spark alive.

00:29:11.030 --> 00:29:12.790
I didn't do it alone.

00:29:14.550 --> 00:29:16.590
Have you decided to go to France?

00:29:19.200 --> 00:29:20.000
Yes, I have.

00:29:21.350 --> 00:29:23.410
There are quite a few projects there.

00:29:25.510 --> 00:29:27.350
I remember
at the entrance of the Cultural Center,

00:29:27.350 --> 00:29:28.750
there were many colorful flags, right?

00:29:28.750 --> 00:29:29.790
It was beautiful.

00:29:30.960 --> 00:29:31.510
Yes.

00:29:32.080 --> 00:29:33.510
Back then, the anniversary celebrations

00:29:33.510 --> 00:29:35.680
were much livelier
than the Spring Festival.

00:29:35.680 --> 00:29:36.720
It was right here

00:29:37.310 --> 00:29:40.240
that we watched the second half
of your performance.

00:29:45.080 --> 00:29:46.450
I remember one year,

00:29:48.310 --> 00:29:50.570
it started snowing particularly early.

00:29:52.110 --> 00:29:55.440
You mean the year
Xiaoman's grandma passed away?

00:30:22.030 --> 00:30:23.480
I realized later on

00:30:28.110 --> 00:30:30.910
that this was the stage
I had performed on the most—

00:30:32.200 --> 00:30:33.590
and the only one.

00:30:35.830 --> 00:30:36.480
Yeah.

00:30:36.960 --> 00:30:39.690
I remember you've never been afraid
of the stage.

00:30:40.270 --> 00:30:41.830
If I'm around a lot of people,

00:30:41.830 --> 00:30:43.030
I get really nervous.

00:30:45.640 --> 00:30:47.030
I'm the exact opposite.

00:30:48.640 --> 00:30:50.500
The more people, the happier I am.

00:30:54.600 --> 00:30:55.960
I remember the day I performed,

00:30:55.960 --> 00:30:57.270
so many people came.

00:31:00.720 --> 00:31:01.590
Director Meng,

00:31:03.500 --> 00:31:04.300
Director Liu,

00:31:05.350 --> 00:31:06.590
Mr. Ding,

00:31:07.240 --> 00:31:08.160
Mrs. Ding,

00:31:08.840 --> 00:31:09.640
and...

00:31:18.680 --> 00:31:20.540
Anyway, a lot of people showed up.

00:31:21.310 --> 00:31:23.110
So many people applauded for me.

00:31:23.440 --> 00:31:24.350
Back then, I thought,

00:31:24.350 --> 00:31:25.610
for the rest of my life,

00:31:26.030 --> 00:31:27.510
I wanted to stay on stage,

00:31:28.400 --> 00:31:29.730
enjoying the applause,

00:31:30.880 --> 00:31:33.360
enjoying... enjoying the spotlight,

00:31:35.030 --> 00:31:36.960
and always having a huge audience.

00:31:40.960 --> 00:31:42.790
I actually went to many theaters

00:31:43.350 --> 00:31:44.550
and cinemas later on.

00:31:45.240 --> 00:31:46.030
But,

00:31:47.990 --> 00:31:49.200
I still think

00:31:51.030 --> 00:31:52.690
our Workers' Cultural Center

00:31:54.000 --> 00:31:56.310
is the best.

00:31:58.920 --> 00:32:01.510
Because the echo here is incredible.

00:32:17.160 --> 00:32:18.550
Not sunlight.

00:32:20.960 --> 00:32:22.110
Not spring rain.

00:32:25.200 --> 00:32:25.880
No.

00:32:28.590 --> 00:32:29.920
These are not enough.

00:32:31.880 --> 00:32:36.270
I must be a kapok tree,
standing beside you.

00:32:37.310 --> 00:32:38.640
As trees,

00:32:40.110 --> 00:32:41.400
we stand together.

00:32:42.840 --> 00:32:45.790
Our roots tightly intertwined underground,

00:32:46.440 --> 00:32:49.270
and our leaves touching in the clouds.

00:32:51.440 --> 00:32:52.970
With every passing breeze,

00:32:53.790 --> 00:32:55.400
we greet each other.

00:33:05.310 --> 00:33:10.480
We share the cold waves, the wind,
the thunder, and the lightning.

00:33:12.090 --> 00:33:16.410
We share the mist,
the drifting clouds, and the rainbow.

00:33:18.550 --> 00:33:20.110
As if forever apart,

00:33:21.790 --> 00:33:24.680
yet bound together for life.

00:33:35.270 --> 00:33:36.750
You still remember it?

00:33:39.200 --> 00:33:40.330
Actually, that day,

00:33:41.640 --> 00:33:43.500
I made my voice hoarse on purpose.

00:33:46.790 --> 00:33:49.920
When I saw you and Xiaoman
standing on the stage that day,

00:33:50.200 --> 00:33:51.460
I really regretted it.

00:33:58.110 --> 00:33:59.750
But maybe that's just youth.

00:34:13.310 --> 00:34:13.989
Youth.

00:34:20.150 --> 00:34:20.760
Xiaodan.

00:34:21.510 --> 00:34:23.550
I remember you said when you were little

00:34:23.550 --> 00:34:25.080
that you loved high places.

00:34:25.190 --> 00:34:26.790
Now your dream has come true.

00:34:26.909 --> 00:34:28.440
You can build skyscrapers.

00:34:28.670 --> 00:34:29.960
Now I realize

00:34:31.110 --> 00:34:32.969
that the buildings I want to build

00:34:33.400 --> 00:34:34.730
aren't about being tall

00:34:34.880 --> 00:34:35.679
or beautiful.

00:34:38.320 --> 00:34:39.719
I just want to build homes

00:34:40.440 --> 00:34:42.699
where people can live with peace of mind.

00:34:49.440 --> 00:34:52.770
Didn't you say you wanted to see
the other side of the bridge?

00:34:53.110 --> 00:34:54.969
Only after going to the other side

00:34:55.150 --> 00:34:56.320
did I realize

00:34:56.800 --> 00:34:57.930
what's on this side.

00:34:58.510 --> 00:35:00.070
The other side is scenery.

00:35:00.360 --> 00:35:02.280
This side is home.

00:35:02.510 --> 00:35:04.370
Your dreams are too complicated.

00:35:04.670 --> 00:35:05.870
Mine is much simpler.

00:35:06.110 --> 00:35:08.480
I just want to stay in my hometown,

00:35:10.070 --> 00:35:11.270
being with my family.

00:35:16.630 --> 00:35:20.630
Staying in one place is much harder

00:35:21.070 --> 00:35:22.110
than going far

00:35:23.000 --> 00:35:24.110
or climbing high.

00:35:25.630 --> 00:35:26.670
It's been a few years
since I was last here,

00:35:26.670 --> 00:35:28.230
hasn't it?

00:35:28.800 --> 00:35:30.190
At least a dozen years.

00:35:31.880 --> 00:35:34.030
We've really come a long way.

00:35:36.590 --> 00:35:38.070
The quicker the leaving,

00:35:38.800 --> 00:35:40.600
the heavier the longing, right?

00:35:42.150 --> 00:35:44.320
When I was in Shanghai, people said

00:35:44.800 --> 00:35:47.530
those without a hometown
feel the most homesick.

00:35:48.590 --> 00:35:51.580
That doesn't apply to us here.

00:35:51.580 --> 00:35:54.190
♪ I've walked through dark alleys, hit
against high walls, fallen into the pond ♪

00:35:54.190 --> 00:35:56.650
All these years,
what I've been holding on to

00:35:56.800 --> 00:35:57.800
is home.

00:35:57.830 --> 00:35:59.150
♪ I've pursued my ideals, hated this body,
and been to the middle of nowhere ♪

00:35:59.150 --> 00:35:59.670
Right?

00:36:00.190 --> 00:36:01.720
It's right under your feet.

00:36:02.150 --> 00:36:03.550
It's not going anywhere.

00:36:03.600 --> 00:36:05.110
♪ Gazing at the moon in a foreign land
in the gap of the city ♪

00:36:05.110 --> 00:36:05.630
Right.

00:36:06.550 --> 00:36:08.670
Our plant is our hometown.

00:36:08.910 --> 00:36:12.070
♪ Wishing only for the credit of one
who has crossed the bridge ♪

00:36:12.070 --> 00:36:13.730
As long as my hometown is here,

00:36:14.800 --> 00:36:15.160
I guess I'm the captain
who will always return,

00:36:15.160 --> 00:36:17.810
♪ Look at the river flowing ♪

00:36:17.840 --> 00:36:19.190
♪ Where will the young man
on the bridge go? ♪

00:36:19.190 --> 00:36:20.670
no matter how far I sail.

00:36:21.250 --> 00:36:24.040
♪ The vibrant spring sees flying birds
and thriving greenery ♪

00:36:24.060 --> 00:36:26.600
♪ But my heart remains the same ♪

00:36:27.140 --> 00:36:27.190
♪ Listen to the wuthering wind
in the fog ♪

00:36:27.190 --> 00:36:28.240
Alright, Captain.

00:36:28.240 --> 00:36:29.630
First Mate is ready.

00:36:29.920 --> 00:36:31.060
We can set sail anytime.

00:36:31.060 --> 00:36:31.590
♪ The one crossing the bridge
has no fear of the road ahead ♪

00:36:31.590 --> 00:36:32.990
Second Mate is ready too,

00:36:33.110 --> 00:36:33.310
just waiting for your orders.

00:36:33.310 --> 00:36:34.620
♪ With the figure fading away ♪

00:36:34.870 --> 00:36:37.290
♪ The reckless youth is gone from now on ♪

00:36:38.760 --> 00:36:39.590
Well then,

00:36:39.610 --> 00:36:40.360
♪ Look at the river flowing ♪

00:36:40.360 --> 00:36:41.160
let's set off.

00:36:42.280 --> 00:36:43.070
♪ Where will the young man
on the bridge go? ♪

00:36:43.070 --> 00:36:43.960
Let's go!

00:36:45.510 --> 00:36:48.300
♪ The vibrant spring sees flying birds
and thriving greenery ♪

00:36:48.320 --> 00:36:50.860
♪ But my heart remains the same ♪

00:36:51.400 --> 00:36:55.290
♪ Listen to the wuthering wind
in the fog ♪

00:36:55.320 --> 00:36:57.550
♪ The one crossing the bridge
has no fear of the road ahead ♪

00:36:57.570 --> 00:36:58.880
♪ With the figure fading away ♪

00:36:58.970 --> 00:37:01.390
♪ The reckless youth is gone from now on ♪

00:37:03.440 --> 00:37:04.980
♪ With the figure fading away ♪

00:37:05.000 --> 00:37:07.350
♪ The reckless youth is gone from now on ♪

00:37:10.060 --> 00:37:13.490
[2012]

00:37:14.670 --> 00:37:15.400
Xia Lei.

00:37:15.760 --> 00:37:17.960
I can barely take it all in along the way.

00:37:17.960 --> 00:37:19.690
Is this really still Tiecheng?

00:37:19.760 --> 00:37:21.360
Is this still our Northeast?

00:37:22.030 --> 00:37:25.110
The state has stepped up efforts
to revitalize the Northeast.

00:37:25.110 --> 00:37:27.060
Many policies
have already been implemented.

00:37:27.060 --> 00:37:29.460
Our Factory No. 3
has benefited from it too.

00:37:29.640 --> 00:37:31.520
You've achieved your dream, kid.

00:37:32.920 --> 00:37:34.780
It's only a preliminary success.

00:37:36.320 --> 00:37:37.800
Regarding our plant's operations,

00:37:37.800 --> 00:37:39.440
channels, and products—

00:37:39.590 --> 00:37:42.190
we can't afford problems
in any of these areas.

00:37:44.030 --> 00:37:45.590
The spirit of our East Chemical Plant

00:37:45.590 --> 00:37:47.710
lives on in you young people.

00:37:47.840 --> 00:37:48.630
Right now,

00:37:48.630 --> 00:37:50.630
I just want to go back
to Factory No. 3 so badly

00:37:50.630 --> 00:37:52.560
and see exactly what it has become.

00:37:59.840 --> 00:38:01.230
Xiaodan, to be honest,

00:38:01.230 --> 00:38:03.250
when you suddenly said
you had new ideas for the project,

00:38:03.250 --> 00:38:04.450
I was really shocked.

00:38:06.000 --> 00:38:08.320
I'm sorry. I got too carried away before.

00:38:09.190 --> 00:38:10.440
I believe this time,

00:38:10.440 --> 00:38:11.550
you can definitely
provide construction workers

00:38:11.550 --> 00:38:13.150
with a good job opportunity.

00:38:13.230 --> 00:38:14.510
I'm curious,

00:38:14.510 --> 00:38:16.770
how did you change
so much all of a sudden?

00:38:19.920 --> 00:38:21.800
Actually, my design concept

00:38:22.000 --> 00:38:23.400
comes from my hometown.

00:38:25.070 --> 00:38:27.880
I went back to the place
I know best a while ago

00:38:27.880 --> 00:38:29.800
and lived there again for a long time.

00:38:29.800 --> 00:38:31.670
Your hometown? Shanghai?

00:38:33.000 --> 00:38:35.400
No, it's a very small place.

00:38:35.920 --> 00:38:38.760
So small you can't even find it on a map.

00:38:39.400 --> 00:38:40.510
Because it's small?

00:38:40.510 --> 00:38:41.360
Very small.

00:38:41.760 --> 00:38:42.630
But...

00:38:43.400 --> 00:38:45.400
it's big enough for the people there—

00:38:45.400 --> 00:38:46.440
and warm enough.

00:38:47.230 --> 00:38:50.360
It was built by my father's generation.

00:38:51.190 --> 00:38:54.670
It was given a special mission
during a special time.

00:38:54.960 --> 00:38:59.190
I witnessed its decline and rebirth.

00:39:00.550 --> 00:39:03.510
There, I also re-understood

00:39:04.230 --> 00:39:06.440
the relationship between architecture
and people,

00:39:06.440 --> 00:39:07.710
time,

00:39:08.590 --> 00:39:09.920
and memory.

00:39:10.630 --> 00:39:11.840
That sounds like quite a story.

00:39:11.840 --> 00:39:14.370
I must visit your hometown
if I get the chance.

00:39:15.920 --> 00:39:17.030
You are welcome to visit.

00:39:17.030 --> 00:39:18.110
When I went back this time,

00:39:18.110 --> 00:39:20.890
I built a culture and creative park
for my hometown.

00:39:20.890 --> 00:39:22.550
Here are some pictures.

00:39:23.800 --> 00:39:25.660
What is the name of your hometown?

00:39:26.280 --> 00:39:28.880
It's called East Chemical Plant.

00:39:40.000 --> 00:39:41.260
Be careful, everyone.

00:39:43.000 --> 00:39:44.320
Watch the steps.

00:39:44.920 --> 00:39:45.590
Be careful.

00:39:46.190 --> 00:39:47.550
This is the life trajectory of our plant

00:39:47.550 --> 00:39:49.110
over the past 40 years.

00:39:49.590 --> 00:39:50.440
In our plant,

00:39:50.440 --> 00:39:52.630
life and production are integrated.

00:39:53.070 --> 00:39:54.320
It's both a plant

00:39:54.880 --> 00:39:56.440
and a small society.

00:39:56.960 --> 00:39:58.320
This is our hometown,

00:39:58.710 --> 00:39:59.510
our home.

00:40:11.670 --> 00:40:14.670
When we first came to
the East Chemical Plant,

00:40:14.920 --> 00:40:15.920
it was just a town.

00:40:15.960 --> 00:40:17.160
It was all wasteland.

00:40:17.710 --> 00:40:20.590
So we built it on site.

00:40:21.030 --> 00:40:24.030
The conditions
were extremely difficult back then.

00:40:24.480 --> 00:40:27.150
The environment, the personnel—

00:40:27.280 --> 00:40:28.510
everything was lacking.

00:40:28.510 --> 00:40:29.400
The workers...

00:40:29.840 --> 00:40:31.840
But our group of people,

00:40:32.230 --> 00:40:33.440
with our own hands,

00:40:33.920 --> 00:40:35.190
built this plant.

00:40:35.630 --> 00:40:37.490
Every brick, every clod of earth,

00:40:37.880 --> 00:40:39.000
and every steel bar,

00:40:39.000 --> 00:40:40.800
was built by us skilled workers,

00:40:40.900 --> 00:40:43.090
bit by bit.

00:40:44.230 --> 00:40:44.920
Xiaodan,

00:40:46.000 --> 00:40:46.710
see?

00:40:47.630 --> 00:40:49.590
The culture and creative park
has been completed.

00:40:49.590 --> 00:40:50.840
Now, children of Third Front Plant workers

00:40:50.840 --> 00:40:53.300
from all over the country
have come to visit—

00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:56.280
Hubei, Jiangxi,

00:40:57.400 --> 00:40:58.320
and Sichuan.

00:40:59.000 --> 00:40:59.590
Xiaodan,

00:40:59.920 --> 00:41:02.110
this space you created is a huge success.

00:41:02.110 --> 00:41:03.480
Many people from out of town,

00:41:03.480 --> 00:41:05.030
when they see our space,

00:41:05.230 --> 00:41:06.550
want to go back and make one too

00:41:06.550 --> 00:41:07.470
to tell people

00:41:07.490 --> 00:41:08.800
their stories.

00:41:09.280 --> 00:41:10.150
Our great designer,

00:41:10.150 --> 00:41:11.710
when will you come back
to inspect the results?

00:41:11.710 --> 00:41:13.400
Yes, come back, Xiaodan.

00:41:13.550 --> 00:41:14.710
We miss you so much.

00:41:15.960 --> 00:41:17.280
Come on. Be careful.

00:41:18.480 --> 00:41:20.070
It's okay. It's okay.

00:41:21.360 --> 00:41:22.000
Okay.

00:41:22.440 --> 00:41:23.110
Don't move.

00:41:24.280 --> 00:41:26.190
Okay, stand still.

00:41:26.240 --> 00:41:26.990
Okay.

00:41:27.800 --> 00:41:29.440
Wait a second. I'm coming up.

00:41:31.150 --> 00:41:32.810
Turn around and walk forward.

00:41:33.230 --> 00:41:33.840
Okay.

00:41:34.510 --> 00:41:35.640
We're almost there.

00:41:35.960 --> 00:41:37.400
Where are you taking me?

00:41:37.400 --> 00:41:38.670
Six more steps.

00:41:38.800 --> 00:41:43.070
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6.

00:41:43.400 --> 00:41:44.200
One more step.

00:41:44.320 --> 00:41:44.920
One more step.

00:41:44.920 --> 00:41:46.590
7, 8. Good.

00:41:47.430 --> 00:41:48.690
Are you standing firm?

00:41:48.800 --> 00:41:49.920
Stand firm. Both feet.

00:41:49.920 --> 00:41:51.180
Together. Stand firm.

00:41:51.960 --> 00:41:53.290
-Alright.
-Stand firm.

00:41:55.510 --> 00:41:56.070
Look.

00:42:00.320 --> 00:42:01.510
It's so beautiful!

00:42:01.530 --> 00:42:03.390
What do you think? Not bad, right?

00:42:04.680 --> 00:42:06.810
The plant is just behind the mountain.

00:42:07.960 --> 00:42:09.070
I used to think...

00:42:10.350 --> 00:42:10.630
♪ Smoke from the chimney drifted
back in those days ♪

00:42:10.630 --> 00:42:12.710
that my world ended here.

00:42:14.650 --> 00:42:15.000
♪ Distant friends waving their hands ♪

00:42:15.000 --> 00:42:16.320
But now I realize...

00:42:17.280 --> 00:42:18.510
the scenery here is actually pretty good.

00:42:18.510 --> 00:42:18.840
Right?

00:42:18.840 --> 00:42:22.730
♪ From some yard wall comes a whistle ♪

00:42:22.920 --> 00:42:24.110
♪ Blowing the years running along ♪

00:42:24.110 --> 00:42:27.320
What I have is good enough.

00:42:27.550 --> 00:42:31.440
♪ You're always on my mind ♪

00:42:31.440 --> 00:42:31.710
Me too.

00:42:31.710 --> 00:42:34.710
♪ How are you doing now? ♪

00:42:34.710 --> 00:42:35.670
Life...

00:42:35.950 --> 00:42:37.830
♪ Would you know me when we meet again? ♪

00:42:37.830 --> 00:42:39.960
doesn't need to be perfectly perfect.

00:42:40.240 --> 00:42:44.350
♪ I grew tall through all the goodbyes ♪

00:42:46.420 --> 00:42:50.160
♪ The one who wept with longing ♪

00:42:50.330 --> 00:42:54.010
♪ Home is where your heart
stays attached ♪

00:42:54.640 --> 00:42:57.190
♪ Those cheeks flushed red in heavy snow ♪

00:42:57.190 --> 00:42:58.940
[The end]

00:42:58.940 --> 00:43:02.920
♪ The smoke that rose to welcome me home ♪

00:43:03.480 --> 00:43:07.430
♪ The one I saw just by turning around ♪

00:43:07.540 --> 00:43:11.080
♪ Home is where the door's left open
for me ♪